CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780171548
OL,3,CSoggy start to June as record-breaking
OL,4,CUK heatwave gives way to thunderstorms
OL,6,FJune is set to begin with rain showers
OL,7,Fseen more widely, broken up by some
OL,8,F"brighter intervals", forecasters said.
OL,10,FMet Office meteorologist Greg Dewhurst
OL,11,Fsaid next week will bring "a change
OL,12,Ffrom the heatwave" as temperatures
OL,13,Ffall closer to average.
OL,15,FHe said: "It's been quite a dry period
OL,16,Fof weather and hot period of weather,
OL,17,Fso it will be probably much needed and
OL,18,Fmuch welcome rain to gardeners and
OL,19,Fgrowers and farmers with the ground
OL,20,Fbeing so dry at the moment.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@TO]sD@[OUtD@RO]wD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1780171548
OL,3,CSoggy start to June as record-breaking
OL,4,CUK heatwave gives way to thunderstorms
OL,6,F"So it is a change, but probably a
OL,7,Fwelcome change for those who either
OL,8,Fdon't like the heat or want some rain."
OL,10,FMr Dewhurst added that there are "good
OL,11,Fsigns" the heat will return, with warm
OL,12,Fspells likely following an "unsettled"
OL,13,Fstart to June.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@gO]rD@bOUsD@FO]tD@\OUtD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
